Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Peel and chop the @potatoes{600%g} into 2cm chunks.

Place the potatoes in a #pot{}. Cover with water, season with @salt{to taste}, bring to the boil and cook until fork tender, ~{12-18%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain the potatoes in a #colander{} (reserving some cooking water) and return to the pot, off the heat.

Add a knob of @butter{to taste} and a splash of @milk{} or cooking water. Mash with a #potato masher{} until smooth. Season with salt and @pepper{to taste}.

Meanwhile, trim the @carrot{1%unit}(coarsely grated, no need to peel).

Peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Place a #stainless steel pan{} over medium-high heat (no oil).

Fry the @Irish lamb mince{240%g} and carrot until browned, ~{5-6%minutes}. Break it up as it cooks.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw mince. Mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Add the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute}.

Stir in @passata{1%pack}, @dried thyme{1%sachet}, @chicken stock{2%sachets}, @Worcester sauce{2%sachets}, @sugar{1/2%tsp} and @water{50%ml}.

Bring to the boil, then lower the heat to medium. Simmer until thickened, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Pour the lamb into an #ovenproof dish{}.

Spread the mash over the top in an even layer, using the back of a #spoon{} to smooth it out.

Sprinkle over the @Italian style hard cheese{1%unit}(grated), then place on the top shelf of the oven.

Cook until golden, ~{5-6%minutes}.

While the pie cooks, chop the @tomato{2}(chopped into 2cm chunks).

Pop the tomato into a #salad bowl{}, together with @salt{½%tsp}, @pepper{to taste} and a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Just before serving, toss the @salad leaves{40%g} with the tomatoes and the dressing.

Once cooked, remove from the oven and leave to stand for a couple of mins.

Share the shepherd's pie between your plates.

Serve the green salad alongside.